main event: A single round object, the size of a quarter at arm's length, appeared to drop, then ascend and disappear over Long Beach, California on July 7, 1952.
interesting points: The object was observed for about 1 minute.
The observer was possibly deemed to have a high degree of reliability.
The description could fit that of jet aircraft activity.
The case was classified as 'Probably Astronomical' in accordance with ATIC Evaluations.
A check with GGC weather balloons showed none in the area at the time of the sighting.
photographs: No, the report does not include any photographs.
